# Systems gameplay quality (studio)

Complements `.cursor/rules/runtime-discipline.mdc` for systems that touch gameplay simulation.

- Prefer data-driven tuning (config, registries, JSON) over magic numbers in hot paths.
- Use delta time (`deltaTime`) for time-based simulation in the frame loop.
- Avoid coupling UI DOM to simulation logic — use events / bus / editor contracts.
- Document which design doc or `design/gdd/` file a feature implements when non-obvious.
- State machines: document states and transitions when behavior is branching.
